  "prompt": "Who are the Impractical Jokers?",
  "response": "The Impractical Jokers are a comedy troupe consisting of four lifelong friends: Joe Gatto, James \"Murr\" Murray, Brian \"Q\" Quinn, and Sal Vulcano. They are best known for their hidden camera reality TV show, also called *Impractical Jokers*, which airs on TruTV. The show premiered in 2011 and has since gained a large following.\n\nThe premise of the show involves the four friends challenging each other to perform outrageous and often embarrassing dares in public, all while being filmed with hidden cameras. The scenarios are designed to test their comfort levels and ability to improvise under awkward or hilarious circumstances. At the end of each episode, the \"loser\" of the challenges faces a punishment, which is typically the most extreme and humiliating task of all.\n\nThe group's chemistry, humor, and willingness to push boundaries have made *Impractical Jokers* a popular and enduring series. In addition to the TV show, they have toured with live comedy performances and have released a movie, *Impractical Jokers: The Movie*, in 2020. Joe Gatto announced his departure from the group in late 2021, but the remaining members have continued with the show and other projects.",
